g.inkscape:label: Layer 1
g.text: Tubing Route Strain Relief Flow running before cannulation
Observe continuous outflow at VAB outlet.

text.tspan: A) Setup + draping (heated platform with midline channel, PressN Seal drape, dorsal 6-9mm vertical midline incision over the scapulae for the VAB implant)
B) Tubing routing to reliev strain (subcutaneous tunnel via trocar, thoracic loop, flow of saline from Pump -> VAB -> Probe -> Outlet/Collection, make clear flow during procedure)
C) Jugular isolation (landmark side vein, two loose ligatures ~34mm apart, hemostats creating partial occlusion + planned venotomy site)
D) Venotomy, insertion & fixation (probe in lumen, tip 12mm past cranial tie, cranial tie around vessel+probe, caudal tie around probe external to vessel)
